beer.beer_description:
A pale beer made with New Zealand hops for a long lasting bitter finish.

Hop as hell is the palest and hoppiest beer that we have ever brewed. As most of our beers tend to be on the malty side, hop as hell was brewed as an alternative and is available throughout the summer months.

A deep red coloured bitter with a sharp, crisp aftertaste

Redwood is a dark red, very flavoursome bitter which we usually brew around christmas time. It has won an award in the past (see picture below) and we still rate it as one of the best beers we have ever brewed.

beer.beer_description:
A Stunning creamy mild

reviving the taste of yesteryear.

We began the Mild back in 2006 with the intention of just doing one or two brews to see how it went, and due to popular demand we carried on making it and it is now a regular on our brewing schedule.

beer.beer_description:
A traditional malt based bitter, an outstanding premium bitter.

Woodlands Best Bitter was the first brew we ever created, based on a home brew recipe created by our founder, John, back in the 1970s. This is just a great traditional best bitter that is loved by all that try it.
